main fig

#ggplot(hetmut) plots Normalized.Signal as a function of Genotype
#geom_point plots individual observations on this plot
#geom_errorbar points to my group means df hetmut_sum1 and the bounds of the mean+/- standard error bar
#the successive geom_point plots the mean; specify color so it does not conflict with the color call in the first geom_point

library(ggplot2)
ggplot(hetmut,aes(x = Genotype,
                 y = Normalized.Signal,
                 fill = Organ,
                 alpha = 1))+
  geom_point(aes(shape = Organ),
             alpha = 2.0,
             size = 2,
             position = position_jitterdodge())+
  geom_boxplot(outlier.shape = NA,
               alpha = 0.1)+
    stat_summary(fun.y = mean, color = "black", position = position_dodge(0.75),width = 0.2,
             geom = "crossbar",
             show.legend = FALSE)+
   geom_errorbar(data = hetmut_sum, aes(ymin=Normalized.Signal-sd,
                     ymax=Normalized.Signal+sd),
                 width=.2,
                 position=position_dodge(0.75))+
  scale_alpha(guide = "none")+
  xlab("Naa10 genotype")+
  ylab("NAA10 signal normalized to
       REVERT total protein stain")+
  theme_bw(base_size = 12, base_family = "Helvetica")
## Warning: The `fun.y` argument of `stat_summary()` is deprecated as of ggplot2 3.3.0.
## ℹ Please use the `fun` argument instead.

Hypothesis testing

unpaired t-test

t.test(Normalized.Signal~Genotype, hetmut)
## 
##  Welch Two Sample t-test
## 
## data:  Normalized.Signal by Genotype
## t = -3.0736, df = 21.448, p-value = 0.005668
## alternative hypothesis: true difference in means between group Naa10 +/- or -/+ and group Naa10 +/+ is not equal to 0
## 95 percent confidence interval:
##  -111512.03  -21577.18
## sample estimates:
## mean in group Naa10 +/- or -/+        mean in group Naa10 +/+ 
##                       41434.99                      107979.60
t.test(Normalized.Signal~Organ, hetmut)
## 
##  Welch Two Sample t-test
## 
## data:  Normalized.Signal by Organ
## t = 3.213, df = 21.018, p-value = 0.004172
## alternative hypothesis: true difference in means between group heart and group liver is not equal to 0
## 95 percent confidence interval:
##   24297.5 113447.2
## sample estimates:
## mean in group heart mean in group liver 
##           109143.47            40271.11

Instead of repeated t-testing, just do ANOVA.

This way I can see if normalized NAA10 signal differs due to genotype, organ, replicate blot or an interaction between genotype and other factors.

Genotype contributes to significant differences in mean normalized NAA10 signal.

Organ is non-significant, but interacts with Genotype to contribute differences in mean normalized NAA10 signal.
